    <item>
      <title>Building Hardware-Enforced Trust into Matter Devices with ESP-TEE</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/2025/09/matter_w_esp_tee_c6/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 12 Sep 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/2025/09/matter_w_esp_tee_c6/</guid>
      <description>As security expectations rise globally - driven by region-specific cybersecurity regulations - safeguarding device credentials has become critical for IoT manufacturers. This article explains how the ESP-TEE framework integrates with Matter and demonstrates building secure products using the Espressif RISC-V SoCs, showcasing hardware-enforced security that can resist scalable remote software attacks.</description>
      <media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="http://localhost:1313/blog/2025/09/matter_w_esp_tee_c6/featured-esp-matter-w-tee.webp" />
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Boot Secure, Restore Smart: Accelerating Device Startup on ESP32</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/2025/07/faster-device-restoration/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 18 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/2025/07/faster-device-restoration/</guid>
      <description>Fast and secure device restoration during boot-up is critical for real-time IoT applications like smart lighting. In this article, we explore how to reduce boot-up delays by restoring device state early, directly from the ESP-IDF bootloader.</description>
